Daniel, he's praying.

00:30:23.919 --> 00:30:27.919
If anyone makes any petition to anyone other than the king,

00:30:27.919 --> 00:30:30.919
den of lions, my God said to pray.

00:30:30.919 --> 00:30:35.919
So I'm going to pray, just as I did before.

00:30:35.919 --> 00:30:37.919
See, obedience requires commitment.

00:30:37.919 --> 00:30:40.919
Turn to the book of Acts, if you will.

00:30:40.919 --> 00:30:46.919
Acts chapter number 5.

00:30:46.919 --> 00:30:50.919
In Acts chapter number 5, I see a measure of commitment

00:30:50.919 --> 00:30:55.919
that is so vital for us this evening to really grasp

00:30:55.919 --> 00:30:59.919
and get a hold of in our hearts.

00:30:59.919 --> 00:31:03.919
The people of God have already begun facing some persecution

00:31:03.919 --> 00:31:05.919
and some difficulty.

00:31:05.919 --> 00:31:11.919
We've read in previous messages about some of that persecution that begins.

00:31:11.919 --> 00:31:14.919
In chapter number 4, you enter into the fifth chapter

00:31:14.919 --> 00:31:20.919
and you continue to see the persecution and the purging, if you will.

00:31:20.919 --> 00:31:25.919
We find that they were put in prison.

00:31:25.919 --> 00:31:28.919
It says in verse number 18 that they laid their hands on the apostles

00:31:28.919 --> 00:31:31.919
and put them in the common prison.

00:31:31.919 --> 00:31:33.919
I love verse number 19,

00:31:33.919 --> 00:31:37.919
but the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors and brought them forth.

00:31:37.919 --> 00:31:39.919
Isn't that wonderful?

00:31:39.919 --> 00:31:43.919
God intervened. God worked.

00:31:43.919 --> 00:31:45.919
The angel of the Lord said to them in verse 20,

00:31:45.919 --> 00:31:49.919
Go stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.

00:31:49.919 --> 00:31:53.919
They'd already been commanded not to speak any longer in His name.

00:31:53.919 --> 00:31:56.919
We find that here they've been delivered.

00:31:56.919 --> 00:31:58.919
The officers came.

00:31:58.919 --> 00:32:00.919
They were told to go get the prisoners.

00:32:00.919 --> 00:32:03.919
In verse number 22, when the officers came and found them not in the prison,

00:32:03.919 --> 00:32:04.919
they returned and told, saying,

00:32:04.919 --> 00:32:06.919
The prison truly found we shut with all safety,

00:32:06.919 --> 00:32:08.919
and the keepers standing without before the doors.

00:32:08.919 --> 00:32:11.919
But when we had opened, we found no man within.

00:32:11.919 --> 00:32:16.919
Now can you imagine these officers telling this to the commanding officer?

00:32:16.919 --> 00:32:19.919
Hold on a minute. What happened here?

00:32:19.919 --> 00:32:22.919
I'm telling you, we got there and it was closed, it was sealed,

00:32:22.919 --> 00:32:25.919
and the guards were outside.

00:32:25.919 --> 00:32:31.919
And we opened the door and there's no one in there.

00:32:31.919 --> 00:32:34.919
God.

00:32:34.919 --> 00:32:35.919
Notice what it says.

00:32:35.919 --> 00:32:38.919
Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priest heard these things,

00:32:38.919 --> 00:32:41.919
they doubted of them whereunto this would grow.

00:32:41.919 --> 00:32:42.919
Then came one and told them, saying,

00:32:42.919 --> 00:32:45.919
Behold, we found them.

00:32:45.919 --> 00:32:46.919
Notice what it says.

00:32:46.919 --> 00:32:51.919
The men whom you put in prison are standing in the temple and teaching the people.

00:32:51.919 --> 00:32:53.919
Isn't that awesome?

00:32:53.919 --> 00:32:56.919
They're doing what God told them to do.

00:32:56.919 --> 00:32:59.919
God said, You're to be my witnesses.

00:32:59.919 --> 00:33:01.919
God said, You're to proclaim my truth.

00:33:01.919 --> 00:33:03.919
And that's what they're doing.

00:33:03.919 --> 00:33:04.919
It says in verse 26,

00:33:04.919 --> 00:33:07.919
Then went the captain with the officers and brought them without violence,

00:33:07.919 --> 00:33:10.919
for they feared the people, lest they should have been stoned.

00:33:10.919 --> 00:33:12.919
And when they had brought them, they set them before the council,

00:33:12.919 --> 00:33:14.919
and the high priest asked them.

00:33:14.919 --> 00:33:16.919
Notice what the high priest asks in verse 28.

00:33:16.919 --> 00:33:25.919
Did not we straightly command you that you should not teach in this name?

00:33:25.919 --> 00:33:31.919
I can almost hear the tone of the high priest.

00:33:31.919 --> 00:33:33.919
Were we not clear?

00:33:33.919 --> 00:33:34.919
Did you not understand?

00:33:34.919 --> 00:33:38.919
Was there something that was ambiguous about what we told you to do?

00:33:38.919 --> 00:33:39.919
You see the high priest.

00:33:39.919 --> 00:33:42.919
Didn't we command you?

00:33:42.919 --> 00:33:45.919
Behold, you have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine.

00:33:45.919 --> 00:33:48.919
Isn't that awesome?

00:33:48.919 --> 00:33:49.919
And look at what it says.

00:33:49.919 --> 00:33:53.919
And intend to bring this man's blood upon us.

00:33:53.919 --> 00:34:00.919
Now, I'm speaking this evening about the fact that obedience requires commitment.

00:34:00.919 --> 00:34:07.919
In this situation, Peter and the disciples, they knew what God had commanded.

00:34:07.919 --> 00:34:10.919
But now there's another command.

00:34:10.919 --> 00:34:11.919
He says in verse number 28,

00:34:11.919 --> 00:34:15.919
Did not we straightly command you?

00:34:15.919 --> 00:34:19.919
What happens when we are faced with two commands?

00:34:19.919 --> 00:34:22.919
We must take heed to the greater command.

00:34:22.919 --> 00:34:23.919
What's the greater command?

00:34:23.919 --> 00:34:25.919
The one with the greater authority.

00:34:25.919 --> 00:34:26.919
Who's the one with all authority?

00:34:26.919 --> 00:34:28.919
Our Savior.

00:34:28.919 --> 00:34:31.919
All power is given unto me in heaven and in earth.

00:34:31.919 --> 00:34:34.919
He has all authority and all power.

00:34:34.919 --> 00:34:35.919
He is God.

00:34:35.919 --> 00:34:37.919
He is the creator and sustainer.

00:34:37.919 --> 00:34:43.919
And so we find that this high priest who has some earthly, some temporal power,

00:34:43.919 --> 00:34:47.919
he says, hey, don't you know that we've commanded you?

00:34:47.919 --> 00:34:50.919
And Peter says,

00:34:50.919 --> 00:34:53.919
Then Peter and the other apostles answered and said,

00:34:53.919 --> 00:35:00.919
We ought to obey God rather than men.

00:35:00.919 --> 00:35:03.919
How many times have we read that verse of Scripture?

00:35:03.919 --> 00:35:08.919
How many times have we said those words of Acts 5 in verse number 29?

00:35:08.919 --> 00:35:10.919
We ought to obey God rather than men.

00:35:10.919 --> 00:35:14.919
Listen, that's not a card that we pull out in convenience

00:35:14.919 --> 00:35:18.919
when we just don't want to obey some other authority.

00:35:18.919 --> 00:35:19.919
Right?

00:35:19.919 --> 00:35:21.919
That's not how that's to be used.

00:35:21.919 --> 00:35:23.919
It's not a situation where some authority,

00:35:23.919 --> 00:35:26.919
we've been living in all kinds of disobedience,

00:35:26.919 --> 00:35:28.919
and then some authority comes and wants to tell us to do something and say,

00:35:28.919 --> 00:35:31.919
We ought to obey God rather than men.

00:35:31.919 --> 00:35:33.919
No, no, no, y'all ain't been obeying God anyway, right?

00:35:33.919 --> 00:35:37.919
That's really what they could say to us.

00:35:37.919 --> 00:35:39.919
But as we look at the Word of God,

00:35:39.919 --> 00:35:43.919
we see that no, they were not using it in that manner.

00:35:43.919 --> 00:35:45.919
And I also would say this.

00:35:45.919 --> 00:35:48.919
When we say that we ought to obey God rather than men,

00:35:48.919 --> 00:35:53.919
it doesn't mean that we should expect it to be a road of ease.

00:35:53.919 --> 00:35:57.919
Rather, we should expect that there's going to be some pressures put on

00:35:57.919 --> 00:36:02.919
to find out how committed we really are to obedience.

00:36:02.919 --> 00:36:05.919
How committed are you to obeying God?

00:36:05.919 --> 00:36:07.919
How committed am I to obeying God?

00:36:07.919 --> 00:36:09.919
Can I say this evening,

00:36:09.919 --> 00:36:11.919
in the United States of America,

00:36:11.919 --> 00:36:15.919
it's actually been really easy to obey God.

00:36:15.919 --> 00:36:20.919
It has been abundantly easy to obey God.

00:36:20.919 --> 00:36:22.919
And if we'd be honest,

00:36:22.919 --> 00:36:26.919
there's a lot of areas where we have fallen short of obeying God.

00:36:26.919 --> 00:36:28.919
But it's been easy.

00:36:28.919 --> 00:36:30.919
We're not going to start obeying God

00:36:30.919 --> 00:36:33.919
when they start telling us we're going to go to jail.

00:36:33.919 --> 00:36:37.919
It doesn't really make sense that we would do that.

00:36:37.919 --> 00:36:41.919
But we find here in Acts chapter 5

00:36:41.919 --> 00:36:44.919
that he not only says we ought to obey God rather than men,

00:36:44.919 --> 00:36:46.919
but he says the God of our fathers raised up Jesus,

00:36:46.919 --> 00:36:48.919
whom He slew and hanged on a tree.

00:36:48.919 --> 00:36:50.919
Listen, we serve a risen Savior.

00:36:50.919 --> 00:36:51.919
Amen?

00:36:51.919 --> 00:36:53.919
We sang this morning, because He lives.

00:36:53.919 --> 00:36:55.919
Him hath God exalted with His right hand

00:36:55.919 --> 00:36:57.919
to be a prince and a Savior,

00:36:57.919 --> 00:37:00.919
for to give repentance to Israel and forgiveness of sins.

00:37:00.919 --> 00:37:02.919
And we are His witnesses of these things.

00:37:02.919 --> 00:37:04.919
And so is also the Holy Ghost,

00:37:04.919 --> 00:37:06.919
whom God hath given to them that obey Him.

00:37:06.919 --> 00:37:08.919
When they heard that, they were cut to the heart

00:37:08.919 --> 00:37:11.919
and took counsel to slay them.

00:37:11.919 --> 00:37:14.919
Listen, just because we say we're ought to obey God rather than men,

00:37:14.919 --> 00:37:16.919
don't expect that the authorities are going to say,

00:37:16.919 --> 00:37:18.919
oh, okay, we didn't understand that.

00:37:18.919 --> 00:37:20.919
Go ahead, carry on.

00:37:20.919 --> 00:37:22.919
It's not going to work that way.

00:37:22.919 --> 00:37:25.919
Right?

00:37:25.919 --> 00:37:29.919
They're ready to kill them.

00:37:29.919 --> 00:37:34.919
Gamaliel steps in and he gives some counsel

00:37:34.919 --> 00:37:37.919
with regard to what they should do.

00:37:37.919 --> 00:37:39.919
We don't have time to develop all of it,

00:37:39.919 --> 00:37:45.919
but he speaks about Theudas in verse number 36.

00:37:45.919 --> 00:37:48.919
He speaks about Judas in verse number 37.

00:37:48.919 --> 00:37:51.919
When he speaks about Theudas in verse 36,

00:37:51.919 --> 00:37:56.919
he spoke about a man that was boasting himself to be somebody.

00:37:56.919 --> 00:38:01.919
See, that's the great difference between the disciples and Theudas.

00:38:01.919 --> 00:38:05.919
We're nobodies serving the King of Kings.

00:38:05.919 --> 00:38:07.919
We're not boasting ourselves to be somebody.

00:38:07.919 --> 00:38:09.919
But we ought not be anyway, right?

00:38:09.919 --> 00:38:11.919
This morning's message.

00:38:11.919 --> 00:38:13.919
It's all about Jesus.

00:38:13.919 --> 00:38:16.919
We're exalting and magnifying Him.

00:38:16.919 --> 00:38:20.919
He speaks of Judas of Galilee in verse number 37.

00:38:20.919 --> 00:38:23.919
And then notice what he says in verse 38.

00:38:23.919 --> 00:38:26.919
And now I say unto you, refrain from these men,

00:38:26.919 --> 00:38:29.919
speaking of the disciples,

00:38:29.919 --> 00:38:33.919
refrain from these men and let them alone,

00:38:33.919 --> 00:38:38.919
for if this counsel or this work be of men, it will come to naught.

00:38:38.919 --> 00:38:40.919
That's true.

00:38:40.919 --> 00:38:42.919
That's what happened with Theudas.

00:38:42.919 --> 00:38:44.919
That's what happened with Judas.

00:38:44.919 --> 00:38:47.919
It came to naught because it was a movement of men.

00:38:47.919 --> 00:38:50.919
But notice what he says in verse 39.

00:38:50.919 --> 00:38:56.919
But if it be of God, he cannot overthrow it,

00:38:56.919 --> 00:39:00.919
lest happily ye be found even to fight against God.

00:39:00.919 --> 00:39:03.919
But then notice what happens in verse number 40.

00:39:03.919 --> 00:39:06.919
It says, and to him they agreed.

00:39:06.919 --> 00:39:09.919
These religious leaders, the high priest giving charge here

00:39:09.919 --> 00:39:12.919
with all that's taking place, they agree with Gamaliel.

00:39:12.919 --> 00:39:16.919
And it says this, that they called the apostles,

00:39:16.919 --> 00:39:18.919
and then notice right in the middle of verse number 40,

00:39:18.919 --> 00:39:21.919
and beaten them.

00:39:21.919 --> 00:39:24.919
I have it underlined in my Bible.

00:39:24.919 --> 00:39:26.919
And beaten them.

00:39:26.919 --> 00:39:31.919
Demanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus

00:39:31.919 --> 00:39:34.919
and let them go.

00:39:34.919 --> 00:39:37.919
We're speaking tonight about obedience requires commitment.

00:39:37.919 --> 00:39:39.919
They've already been in prison,

00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:41.919
but they're committed to obey.

00:39:41.919 --> 00:39:44.919
They get supernaturally delivered from prison,

00:39:44.919 --> 00:39:47.919
and they're teaching and preaching in His name.

00:39:47.919 --> 00:39:49.919
And then they're called before the council,

00:39:49.919 --> 00:39:52.919
and the council's ready to slay them,

00:39:52.919 --> 00:39:55.919
and Gamaliel intercedes, but they're beating them.

00:39:55.919 --> 00:39:57.919
And so the apostles are beaten,

00:39:57.919 --> 00:39:59.919
and then they're commanded again.

00:39:59.919 --> 00:40:03.679
And again, that they should not speak in the name of Jesus.

00:40:03.679 --> 00:40:05.299
And it says in v. 41,

00:40:05.299 --> 00:40:08.299
and they departed from the presence of the council,

00:40:08.299 --> 00:40:13.679
rejoicing that they were counted worthy

00:40:13.679 --> 00:40:16.559
to suffer shame for His name.

00:40:16.559 --> 00:40:18.559
And then read v. 42.

00:40:18.559 --> 00:40:23.859
And daily, in the temple and in every house,

00:40:23.859 --> 00:40:32.159
they ceased not to preach, to teach, and preach Jesus Christ.

00:40:32.159 --> 00:40:35.419
That is a commitment to obedience.

00:40:35.419 --> 00:40:36.659
Amen?

00:40:36.659 --> 00:40:38.959
Obedience is critical.

00:40:38.959 --> 00:40:42.299
Obedience requires commitment.

00:40:42.299 --> 00:40:44.959
See, when we truly understand who God is

00:40:44.959 --> 00:40:47.799
and we understand His authority in our lives,

00:40:47.799 --> 00:40:50.299
we say, I'm going to obey God.

00:40:50.299 --> 00:40:54.799
There's really no other option for me but to obey God.

00:40:54.799 --> 00:40:56.119
I understand I can disobey,

00:40:56.119 --> 00:40:59.579
but as I'm considering it spiritually,

00:40:59.579 --> 00:41:02.299
as I'm looking at the truth of God's Word,

00:41:02.299 --> 00:41:07.099
why would I want to disobey?

00:41:07.099 --> 00:41:11.599
I understand this evening that we're humans and we struggle,

00:41:11.599 --> 00:41:15.399
but the reality is that in the power of God and with His help,

00:41:15.399 --> 00:41:20.019
we ought to say, I'm going to obey God.

00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:21.659
I'm going to obey God.

00:41:21.659 --> 00:41:24.579
And the commitment to obedience

00:41:24.579 --> 00:41:29.419
that we see in Acts 5 is convicting to me.

00:41:29.419 --> 00:41:31.419
It's convicting to me.

00:41:31.419 --> 00:41:33.619
And I look at this passage of Scripture

00:41:33.619 --> 00:41:38.719
and I wonder tonight how committed am I to obeying God?

00:41:38.719 --> 00:41:40.639
I've already said it,

00:41:40.639 --> 00:41:44.339
it's been easy in our nation to obey God.

00:41:44.339 --> 00:41:47.339
I made this statement a few Sundays ago.

00:41:47.339 --> 00:41:50.659
I believe it was July 3rd, so a month ago.

00:41:50.659 --> 00:41:53.019
I made the statement that we could go out after church

00:41:53.019 --> 00:41:56.919
and we can preach and we can give Gospel tracts

00:41:56.919 --> 00:41:59.059
and we don't have to have any fear.

00:41:59.059 --> 00:42:01.619
No one's going to do anything to us.

00:42:01.619 --> 00:42:04.219
I made that statement on July 3rd, Sunday morning,

00:42:04.219 --> 00:42:05.819
preaching from this pulpit,

00:42:05.819 --> 00:42:08.299
