I read a story about a man that said,

00:42:52.359 --> 00:42:54.739
man, I want God's blessing on my finances

00:42:54.739 --> 00:42:57.999
and I'm going to tithe and I'm going to give to God's work

00:42:57.999 --> 00:43:00.859
and I'm going to make this commitment.

00:43:02.279 --> 00:43:05.119
And all of a sudden, he didn't have an abundance anymore.

00:43:06.319 --> 00:43:08.159
Well, I just don't think I can afford to do it.

00:43:08.159 --> 00:43:09.279
Did God change?

00:43:10.639 --> 00:43:11.959
I'm going to make a commitment

00:43:11.959 --> 00:43:14.119
that I'm going to be a bold witness.

00:43:14.119 --> 00:43:17.599
I'm going to share the gospel of Jesus Christ with people.

00:43:17.599 --> 00:43:20.399
All of a sudden, you make that commitment

00:43:20.399 --> 00:43:23.199
and someone's going, hey, you can't talk about that here.

00:43:24.699 --> 00:43:25.859
Somebody's going to slam a door.

00:43:25.859 --> 00:43:27.759
Somebody's going to, I'm going to call the police.

00:43:27.759 --> 00:43:32.419
They're going to, why are we committed to obeying God?

00:43:33.759 --> 00:43:38.259
Listen, this evening, when we think about the word of God,

00:43:39.259 --> 00:43:43.139
this book is more authoritative

00:43:43.139 --> 00:43:46.639
than any other document on the face of the earth.

00:43:49.059 --> 00:43:52.979
Any other document, this book is superior.

00:43:52.979 --> 00:43:55.019
And so I ought to obey God.

00:43:55.019 --> 00:43:57.899
If I want God's blessing, and I do,

00:43:57.899 --> 00:44:00.359
I believe that we want God's blessing,

00:44:00.359 --> 00:44:02.199
we better get back to obedience.

00:44:03.179 --> 00:44:07.559
Not taking the approach of Saul in 1 Samuel 15,

00:44:08.379 --> 00:44:11.739
and excusing our disobedience,

00:44:11.739 --> 00:44:15.579
justifying our partial obedience.

00:44:15.579 --> 00:44:18.819
Well, we were going to do this, and I was going to do that.

00:44:18.819 --> 00:44:20.859
God says, no, no, no, what did I say?

00:44:22.219 --> 00:44:24.019
That's not what I told you to do, Saul.

00:44:24.019 --> 00:44:25.379
I was clear.

00:44:25.379 --> 00:44:26.219
When we go to the word of God,

00:44:26.219 --> 00:44:29.499
listen, if we really want to know what God wants us to do,

00:44:29.499 --> 00:44:30.399
we can find it.

00:44:32.239 --> 00:44:34.519
If we want to justify our disobedience,

00:44:35.939 --> 00:44:37.499
you know what I found in life?

00:44:37.499 --> 00:44:40.679
We can figure out a way to do it, just like Saul did.

00:44:42.619 --> 00:44:44.419
And this evening, we just make a commitment.

00:44:44.419 --> 00:44:45.259
Why?

00:44:46.099 --> 00:44:48.099
Because to obey is better.

00:44:48.099 --> 00:44:50.319
To obey is better.

00:44:51.299 --> 00:44:54.259
It is critical, obedience is critical.

00:44:54.259 --> 00:44:57.179
But obedience requires commitment.

00:44:57.179 --> 00:44:59.779
I wonder tonight, how committed am I

00:44:59.779 --> 00:45:01.499
to obeying the word of God?

00:45:01.499 --> 00:45:04.819
I mean, I'm not talking about when it's easy to obey,

00:45:04.819 --> 00:45:06.819
when it's convenient to obey.

00:45:06.819 --> 00:45:08.899
When everyone else is obeying.

00:45:08.899 --> 00:45:11.379
I'm talking about when the pressure comes.

00:45:12.499 --> 00:45:16.899
When it no longer is easy, when it no longer is convenient.

00:45:18.099 --> 00:45:19.499
Am I still going to obey God?

00:45:20.619 --> 00:45:23.739
When they say, hey, listen, you keep preaching that way,

00:45:23.739 --> 00:45:25.699
and here's what's going to happen.

00:45:25.699 --> 00:45:27.219
What do you do?

00:45:27.219 --> 00:45:28.059
Where do you go?

00:45:29.119 --> 00:45:30.899
God is able.

00:45:30.899 --> 00:45:34.199
I just got to trust and obey.

00:45:34.199 --> 00:45:35.039
Let's pray.

00:45:35.039 --> 00:45:36.579
Father, we love you.

00:45:37.339 --> 00:45:39.059
Thank you for loving us.

00:45:39.059 --> 00:45:41.219
Thank you for the precious word of God.

00:45:43.659 --> 00:45:46.059
I thank you for the subject matter this evening.

00:45:46.999 --> 00:45:48.659
I thank you for how you've used your word

00:45:48.659 --> 00:45:50.759
to convict me in my life.

00:45:53.819 --> 00:45:56.979
God, I pray that we'd take a few moments this evening

00:45:57.939 --> 00:46:00.819
to really evaluate our lives.

00:46:02.259 --> 00:46:06.339
I think about what Mary said to those servants

00:46:07.099 --> 00:46:07.939
in John 2.

00:46:10.379 --> 00:46:12.499
Speaking of Jesus, she said to those servants,

00:46:12.499 --> 00:46:14.439
whatsoever he saith unto you, do.

00:46:16.299 --> 00:46:20.279
God, I pray that we'd have that type of obedient heart.

00:46:21.919 --> 00:46:24.619
That, Lord, I will obey.

00:46:26.659 --> 00:46:29.419
You've given us your word, and we're so thankful for it.

00:46:30.419 --> 00:46:35.419
I pray that we'd get back to the matter of obedience,

00:46:36.659 --> 00:46:41.659
that we'd live, walk in obedience, that you would bless.

00:46:44.579 --> 00:46:47.259
I pray that if there's some specific area,

00:46:48.099 --> 00:46:49.539
I've only mentioned a few,

00:46:49.539 --> 00:46:53.179
but perhaps there's some specific area in our lives

00:46:53.179 --> 00:46:57.739
that the Holy Spirit of God would just prick our hearts.

00:46:57.739 --> 00:46:59.379
We ask you to do that, Lord,

00:47:02.139 --> 00:47:03.739
that we'd get it right with you,

00:47:04.699 --> 00:47:07.399
that we'd renew that commitment to obedience,

00:47:08.299 --> 00:47:09.859
and see your hand of blessing.

00:47:10.739 --> 00:47:12.259
We pray that in the next few moments,

00:47:12.259 --> 00:47:15.339
as we have opportunity to respond,

00:47:15.339 --> 00:47:16.899
I pray that you'd bless, that you'd move.

00:47:16.899 --> 00:47:19.259
We pray that you'd be glorified.

00:47:19.259 --> 00:47:21.499
For it's in Christ's name we pray, would you.

